# CRLF + comment variant of the complete-set control: a Windows-authored .m3u
# (CRLF line endings, #EXTM3U header, a # comment line) with every disc present must
# flow clean — detection is --check-rom now (the engine census owns completeness), and
# the CRLF-tolerant m3u parsing that REMAINS in the hook (m3u_for + the launch gates)
# must not trip on the file: complete=1 -> no --fetch-next-disc, no --download, exit 0.
desc fetch hook (lodor#7): complete CRLF+comment .m3u -> no disc fetch at all
invoke prehook
config paired
romarg Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u
sdtext Roms/PlayStation (PS)/✓ FF7.m3u	#EXTM3U\r\n# burned on Windows\r\nFF7/D1.chd\r\nFF7/D2.chd\r\n
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D1.chd
sdfile+ Roms/PlayStation (PS)/FF7/D2.chd
engine 0|RESULT complete=1 discs_total=2 discs_present=2
engine 0|
expect_exit 0
expect_trace ENGINE --check-rom
expect_trace_absent ENGINE --fetch-next-disc
expect_trace_absent ENGINE --download
